{"id":"8610","title":"4 Traditional Rice Varieties 🍚| Festive Season | Ugadi Special 🍃🍃","timestamp":"Sat, 17 Mar 2018 01:52:56 +0000","link":"https://ramyarecipesblog.wordpress.com/2018/03/16/4-traditional-rice-varieties-%f0%9f%8d%9a-festive-season-ugadi-special-%f0%9f%8d%83%f0%9f%8d%83/","content":"Authentic and traditional rice recipes on festive season \" Ugadi \" . It's our new year in south India, India 🇮🇳\n\nWe celebrate this festival by wearing new clothes, making new wishes, visiting temple, preparing  \"<i><b>Ugadi Pachadi</b></i>\", savory snacks and mouthwatering sweets 🍧\n\nUgadi Pachadi: it is a combination of '<b><i>shadruchullu</i></b>' means '6 flavours' contains sweet, sour, salt, spicy, tangy and bitter. It means in life all these six flavours includes in anyone's life, so 6 flavours of life.\n\nYou can checkout my recipes for sweets and savory varieties. All my recipes are designed and explained in step by step process it's easy to refer and follow. Some of the best links shared at the end of this post.\n\nToday, I'm sharing simple and aromatic South Indian traditional rice dishes, which we usually make during festivals, I hope you like it and do try 👍\n\n<b>Rice Varieties :</b>\n<strong>\n<a href=\"https://ramyarecipesblog.wordpress.com/2017/08/06/prasadam-pulihora-temple-style-pulihora-tamarind-rice/\"> Pulihora </a></strong>\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-8618\" src=\"https://ramyarecipesblog.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/img_5707.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_5707\" width=\"1462\" height=\"2048\" />\n<strong>\n<a href=\"https://ramyarecipesblog.wordpress.com/2017/10/16/coconut-rice-%F0%9F%8D%9A-lunch-diwali/\"> Coconut Rice </a></strong>\n\n<strong><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-8622\" src=\"https://ramyarecipesblog.files.wordpress.com/2018/03/img_5711.jpg\" alt=\"IMG_5711\" width=\"1462\" height=\"2048\" />\n<strong>\n<a href=\"https://ramyarecipesblog.wordpress.com/2017/12/02/south-indian-thali-andhra-bhojanam-%F0%9F%98%80-veg-sout